<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4677348>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. Arrangement of supralabials in: A. Holotype of Asthenodipsas ingeri sp. nov. (MCZ R43592) from Lumu Lumu, Mount Kinabalu, Sabah. B. Adult Asthenodipsas cf. ingeri sp. nov. (LSUDPC 12633) from Payeh Maga Highlands, Sarawak. C & D. Adults of A. ingeri sp. nov. from Kinabalu National Park, Sabah (LSUDPC 12634 & 12636 respectively). E. Adult A. vertebralis (LSUHC 11709) from Bukit Larut, Perak. F. Asthenodipsas vertebralis (ZRC 2.6619) from Gunung Berumput, Sarawak. Figures not to scale. (Photographs by Evan Quah [A & E], Chien C. Lee [B], Jannico Kelk [C], Björn Lardner [D], & Kelvin K.P. Lim [F])." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4677348/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4677352>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 5. Arrangement of scales on the underside of head in: A. Holotype of Asthenodipsas ingeri sp. nov. (MCZ R43592) from Lumu Lumu, Mount Kinabalu, Sabah. B. Adult Asthenodipsas ingeri sp. nov. (LSUDPC 12636) from Kinabalu National Park, Sabah. C. Asthenodipsas vertebralis (ZRC 2.6619) from Gunung Berumput, Sarawak. D. Adult A. vertebralis (LSUHC 12758) from Genting Highlands, Pahang. Figures not to scale. IL = infralabials, M = mental, SaIM = single anterior inframaxillary, pIM = pairs of posterior inframaxillaries. (Photographs by Evan Quah [A & D], Björn Lardner [B], & Kelvin K.P. Lim [C])." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4677352/files/figure.png" .
